      "instruction": "<p>Combine <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>dried oregano </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) with the <strong>lamb mince</strong>, <strong>chopped shallot</strong>,<strong> ground cinnamon</strong>,<strong> dried thyme </strong>and a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>in a medium bowl</p><p>Give everything a good mix up until thoroughly combined (clean hands is the best way!) – this is your<strong> lamb mixture</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>lamb mixture</strong> into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> and press it onto each <strong>skewer</strong> to form a long sausage shape – these are your<strong> lamb skewers</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1678302880499-x200.jpg",
