        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice<strong> the cucumber </strong>into rounds (as finely as you can!), then add them to a medium bowl with the <strong>remaining oregano</strong>,<strong> sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> sugar </strong>– this is your<strong> oregano cucumber salad</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>(not a big garlic fan? Try using less!), 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a generous crack of <strong>black pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>garlic mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
